Humans have been genetically modifying plants and animals for thousands of years.

7
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:51,600
Maybe a few of your crops had very good yields, maybe one of your wolves was especially loyal.

8
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:56,400
So you did the smart thing and bred the plants and animals that had traits beneficial to you.

9
00:00:57,360 --> 00:01:03,760
Traits are just an expression of genes. So with each generation, those genes got more pronounced.

10
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:10,720
After thousands of years, almost every single plant and animal around us is vastly different

11
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:16,320
from its pre-domesticated state. If humans have been changing genes for millennia, what makes a

12
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:23,040
so-called genetically modified organism, or GMO, different? Selective breeding is basically hoping

13
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:28,800
for lucky hits. Genetic engineering eliminates this factor. We can choose the traits we want,

14
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:35,280
make fruit grow bigger, immune to pests, and so on. So why are people concerned about them?

15
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:43,280
Let's start with one of the most common objections to GMOs.

16
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:49,360
Gene flow, meaning GM crops could mix with traditional crops and introduce unwanted new

17
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:54,320
characteristics into them. There is a method that might guarantee complete prevention,

18
00:01:54,320 --> 00:02:01,520
but is a big anti-GMO argument by itself. Terminator seeds. The idea is that they could

19
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:07,840
produce sterile plants requiring farmers to buy new seeds every year. The very concept of this,

20
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:11,680
however, caused a public outcry, stopping the technology being put to use.

21
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:19,120
This brings us back to the unintentional spreading of engineered DNA. There have been

22
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:24,000
cases of GMOs growing where they weren't planted and traces of modified genes found in foreign

23
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:31,680
crops. But GM plants can't run wild entirely. Many crops pollinate themselves and all crops have to

24
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:36,720
be related to mingle. There are also cultural methods like buffer zones to keep unintentional

25
